  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IDDO DA IDDO  (FACE TO FACE): PROMOTING PEACEFUL RELATIONSHIPS BETWEEN COMMUNITIES AND VIGILANTE GROUPS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A collaborative project implementation strategy is developed with inputs from all relevant stakeholders

CJTF members and community leaders have improved understanding of the positive role of CJTF in building community peace

Peaceful coexistence between civilians and CJTF is promoted at the community level 

Collaboration between civilians and CJTF on local security problems is strengthened</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Alert believes that it is vital to work strategically with the CJTF to promote their positive role as community peacekeepers and prevent them from turning into villains who use similar violent and intimidation tactics as the insurgents themselves.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Joint community-CJTF peacebuilding initiatives contribute to social cohesion in Maiduguri</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">members of the CJTF and community members</narrative>
  </description>
